---
import SplitSection from "../components/SplitSection.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Ice1 from "../assets/Ice-1.svg";
import Ice2 from "../assets/Ice-2.svg";
import Ice3 from "../assets/Ice-3.svg";
import Ice4 from "../assets/Ice-4.svg";
import Ice5 from "../assets/Ice-5.svg";
import Ice6 from "../assets/Ice-6.svg";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Timer from "../assets/material-time.svg";
import Group from "../assets/material-group.svg";
---

<Layout>
  <Header />
  <SplitSection fullHeight={false}>
    <div slot="text">
      <h1>
        Ice Time is a mobile app for figure skaters to reserve freestyle ice
        when traveling.
      </h1>
      <div class="nested-container1">
        <div class="icon-column-s">
          <Image src={Timer} alt="diagnol arrow" />
        </div>
        <div class="body-column-s">
          <p>The design was done in 3 weeks including the style guide</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="nested-container2">
        <div class="icon-column-s">
          <Image src={Group} alt="diagnol arrow" />
        </div>
        <div class="body-column">
          <p>Me, the UI Designer</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div slot="image">
      <Image
        src={Ice1}
        alt="an image of a mobile screen with freestyle sessions to choose from and a skater at the top."
        width={Ice1.width}
        height={Ice1.height}
        class="image"
      />
    </div>
  </SplitSection>
  <SplitSection fullHeight={false}>
    <div slot="text">
      <h1>What prompted this project?</h1>
      <div class="nested-container1">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>A personal problem</h2>
          <p>
            I’m a figure skater who likes to train even when on vacation.
            Recently I went to Austin, Tx with my dad and tried to reserve
            freestyle ice, but the rink’s calendar and booking system were so
            confusing that I chose a different rink.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="nested-container2">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>The idea</h2>
          <p>
            I thought it would be easier to have one app that I can reserve
            practice ice at any rink to avoid interacting with some ice rinks
            poorly designed websites.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div slot="image">
      <Image
        src={Ice2}
        alt="an image of a mobile screen with the booking site for chaprel ice rink that I encountered"
        width={Ice2.width}
        height={Ice2.height}
        class="image"
      />
    </div>
  </SplitSection>
  <SplitSection fullHeight={false}>
    <div slot="text">
      <h1>Early Version of the app</h1>
      <div class="nested-container1">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>Booking app for everything including skating</h2>
          <p>
            This started as challenge to design a booking site within 24 hours.
            The idea was to book an appointment with any business or service,
            but that was very unrealistic, so I niched down and focused on
            Figure skating only.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div slot="image">
      <Image
        src={Ice3}
        alt="two mobile screens from the early version of the app showing options to book from different activites other than ice skating"
        width={Ice3.width}
        height={Ice3.height}
        class="image"
      />
    </div>
  </SplitSection>
  <SplitSection fullHeight={false}>
    <div slot="text">
      <h1>Searching for Rinks</h1>
      <div class="nested-container1">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>Modified Version of the app</h2>
          <p>
            The app home opens to Google Map for ice rinks, so skaters can
            immediately find what they’re looking for.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="nested-container2">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>UI reflects skating aesthetics</h2>
          <p>
            The cool blue color reflects the cold and the subtle loop background
            represents the figures on the ice.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div slot="image">
      <Image
        src={Ice4}
        alt="a mobile screen showing Google map type search feature for ice rinks"
        width={Ice4.width}
        height={Ice4.height}
        class="image"
      />
    </div>
  </SplitSection>
  <SplitSection fullHeight={false}>
    <div slot="text">
      <h1>Skaters save time when they arrive at the rink</h1>
      <div class="nested-container1">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>Instead of standing in line, they pay online</h2>
          <p>
            All rinks require a standard safety waiver. After they sign it and
            pay in the app, it generates a QR code to scan at the rink.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="nested-container2">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>Transferring info to the rink</h2>
          <p>
            The QR code stores the signed waiver and payment info. The skater
            scans the QR code when entering the rink, skipping the line and
            going straight to practice.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div slot="image">
      <Image
        src={Ice5}
        alt="two mobile screens showing the waiver to sign and a QR code once completed"
        width={Ice5.width}
        height={Ice5.height}
        class="image"
      />
    </div>
  </SplitSection>
  <div class="standaloneimg">
    <Image
      src={Ice6}
      alt="a style guide showing the colors I used and their hex codes as well as the font types and roundness of button corners"
      width={Ice6.width}
      height={Ice6.height}
      class="image"
    />
  </div>
  <SplitSection fullHeight={false}>
    <div slot="text">
      <h1>Outcome</h1>
      <div class="nested-container1">
        <div class="body-column">
          <h2>Pitched My Idea to USFS and ISU</h2>
          <p>
            The only way this app could work in real life is if all rinks use
            it. That requires a reputable source to promote it. I emailed the
            major skating organizations to pitch my idea, but my email was
            rejected as spam.
          </p>
          <button
            onclick="window.open('https://www.figma.com/proto/airnBsCh4u3jvqGJay24kV/Ice-Time?page-id=0%3A1&node-id=1-4&p=f&viewport=718%2C91%2C0.1&t=SaQPNZrGNxVt0RSH-1&scaling=scale-down&content-scaling=fixed&starting-point-node-id=1%3A4&show-proto-sidebar=1', '_blank', 'noopener,noreferrer')"
          >
            Try the Prototype
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div slot="image">
      <iframe
        style="border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);"
        width="800"
        height="450"
        src="https://embed.figma.com/proto/airnBsCh4u3jvqGJay24kV/Ice-Time?page-id=0%3A1&node-id=1-4&p=f&viewport=718%2C91%2C0.1&scaling=scale-down&content-scaling=fixed&starting-point-node-id=1%3A4&show-proto-sidebar=1&embed-host=share"
        allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </div>
  </SplitSection>
</Layout>
<style>
  .standaloneimg {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }
  .image {
    height: 600px;
    width: auto;
  }
  .icon-column-s img {
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
  }
  iframe {
    display: block;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .image {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
    }

    iframe {
      display: none;
    }
    Header {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column-reverse;
    }
  }
</style>
